{"author":{"id":"da716b1b2bb7c4bd43933011d646d88072af8c9146b7c99448f1db70c0450347"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1757664560,"nonce":"2ex4FLdVQciyFMnDLHdA08UydH4=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s7LNvX3","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/7270","origin":"github"},"title":"Installation of BEAST on Galaxy Europe","message":"Dear IUC tool development group,\n\nFollowing a discussion I have just add on the GalaxyHelp hub (see the topic here -\u003e https://help.galaxyproject.org/t/installation-of-beast-on-galaxy-europe/16250), I am contacting you to check if it would be worth considering (and not to complex) to install the software BEAST 2 (and potentially  BEAST as well), on Galaxy Europe.\n\nI am not knowledgeable with how to install BEAST on servers (and all the more on a Galaxy server) as I always used it on a server dedicated to phylogeney with a graphical interface (CIPRES Science Gateway). But all should be (neatly) explained on BEAST website (https://www.beast2.org/), with everything on the sourcecode Git page (https://github.com/CompEvol/beast2).\n\nIn terms of graphical interface, nearly nothing is needed (you can check how they did in CIPRES btw): input (.xml) files can be built locally (using Beauti, a java applet) and the BEAST launcher (and potentially the TreeAnnotator and LogCombiner tools of the BEAST package) would be the sole tool to install.\n\nBEAST would be a fantastic add on to the tools that are already on Galaxy Europe as it is one of the most used phylogenetic software that has the unrivaled interest of allowing to infer dates of divergence for phylogenetic trees. It is very widely used by the whole community that works on evolution (and in particular on the timing of evolution).\n\nIf you need additional information, please do not hesitate to ask me, I would be happy to help!\n\nBest,\nXavier Aubriot (phylogenetician/botanist that is very attached to the Galaxy project and its philosophy)","files":null}]}